org.hps.readout.util.collection

Class LCIOCollection<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hps.readout.util.collection.LCIOCollection<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - - The object type of the data stored by the collection.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<LCIOCollection<T>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ManagedLCIOCollection

    public class LCIOCollection<T>
extends Object
implements Comparable<LCIOCollection<T>>
    Class LCIOCollection represents a data collection for use in the LCIO framework. It contains all of the information needed to create and write an LCSim event to an LCIO file.

    • Method Detail

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(LCIOCollection<T> otherCollection)
        Compares two LCIO collections. They are sorted by object type, collection name, and flags in this order. Note that the production driver is not required to match.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface Comparable<LCIOCollection<T>>
        Parameters:
        otherCollection - - The collection to which this object will be compared.
        Returns:
        Returns a value of 0 if the collections are identical (ignoring the production driver). Otherwise, a non-zero value will be returned based on the differing values.
